# Autopus Branding Formats

> Format specifications for Autopus visual feedback and progress displays.
> These formats MUST be used by all agents as defined per subcommand context.

> **Canonical Source**: This file is the single source of truth for all Autopus visual output formats.
> All agents and rules MUST reference this file rather than duplicating format definitions inline.

---

## A0: Session Start Format

Display on the first response of a new conversation (Tier 1 вҖ” Session Start).

**Case 1: SPECs exist**

```
рҹҗҷ Autopus в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ
  н”„лЎңм қнҠё: {project-name} | лӘЁл“ң: {mode}
  SPEC: {draft}к°ң draft В· {approved}к°ң approved В· {implemented}к°ң кө¬нҳ„мӨ‘ В· {completed}к°ң мҷ„лЈҢ
  мөңк·ј мҷ„лЈҢ: {SPEC-ID} ({title})
  лӢӨмқҢ: {next-step recommendation}
```

**Case 2: No SPECs**

```
рҹҗҷ Autopus в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ
  н”„лЎңм қнҠё: {project-name} | лӘЁл“ң: {mode}
  SPEC: м—ҶмқҢ
  лӢӨмқҢ: /auto plan "кё°лҠҘ м„ӨлӘ…" мңјлЎң мӢңмһ‘н•ҳм„ёмҡ”
```

**Field mappings:**
- `{project-name}` вҖ” project name from autopus.yaml
- `{mode}` вҖ” current mode (full, lite, etc.) from autopus.yaml
- `{draft}` вҖ” count of SPECs in draft status
- `{approved}` вҖ” count of SPECs in approved status
- `{implemented}` вҖ” count of SPECs currently being implemented
- `{completed}` вҖ” count of SPECs fully completed
- `{SPEC-ID}` вҖ” identifier of most recently completed SPEC (e.g., `SPEC-UX-001`)
- `{title}` вҖ” title of most recently completed SPEC
- `{next-step recommendation}` вҖ” contextual suggestion based on project state

**Rules:**
- R1: Show Case 1 format when any SPECs exist in the project
- R2: Show Case 2 format when no SPECs exist
- R3: "мөңк·ј мҷ„лЈҢ" line is omitted when no completed SPECs exist

